issues.description:
There is very dangerous vehicle and motorbike speeding along North Capitol street in the underpass tunnel between Rhode Island ave and T street bridge. 

The tunnel is being used as a race track at all times of day and night when there is low traffic. This is incredibly hazardous for DC residents living along North Capitol and residential neighbourhood abutting the street. I have personally witnessed several times vehicles going well above the 25 mile per hour limit towards 70-90 miles per hour. 

In particular this 

- is extremely dangerous for pedestrians, families and children accessing the nearby schools. Drivers speed very aggressively. 
- creates extremely loud noise hitting dangerous levels of 90-100 decibels as the sound crescendos and bounces up the stone walls of the underpass. This is based on a decibel reading from DecibelX app.
- added vehicle exhaust and air pollution. 

Request DDOT to place permanent automated enforcement speed cameras at North Capitol and T street and Rhode Island intersection underpasses so as to enforce the LAW, and support Vision Zero. 

This type of solution already exists in DC and it works very and it provides the added benefit of extra revenue for the City!!!

Please, please, please help enforce the DC law that protects people - not cars!!!!
issues.address: North Capitol Street Northwest Washington, DC 20001, United States of America
